sql:
SELECT DISTINCT researchers.researcher_name
FROM researchers
INNER JOIN model_comments ON researchers.researcher_id = model_comments.researcher_id;

external_knowledge:
- 'Convolutional neural networks' is a common term for models of type 'CNN';
- 'Developed' in this context refers to the creation of models by researchers;
- 'Identities of the creators' points to the names of the researchers;
- 'Names of the convolutional neural networks' refers to the model names.

sql:
SELECT DISTINCT r.researcher_name
FROM researchers r
JOIN model_access ma ON r.researcher_id = ma.researcher_id;

SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT researcher_id) 
FROM model_access 
WHERE model_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
- "creative minds" refers to researchers;
- "gardens" and "seeds of innovation" metaphorically represent the models created by researchers;
- "how many seeds of innovation each has planted" refers to the count of models created by each researcher.

